OL,7,FUnions have threatened to keep staging
OL,8,Fmass co-ordinated strike days until
OL,9,Fsummer as part of long-term plans to
OL,10,Fpressure the Government to agree to
OL,11,Fincreased pay offers.
OL,13,FMark Serwotka, chief of the Public and
OL,14,FCommercial Services Union (PCS) which
OL,15,Frepresents around 100,000 striking
OL,16,Fcivil servants, said walkouts would
OL,17,Fcontinue until at least the summer,
OL,18,Fincluding co-ordinated action, while
OL,19,Funion representatives for train drivers
OL,20,Fand teachers vowed to keep going "for
OL,21,Fas long as it takes."
OL,3,CUnion chiefs threaten mass co-ordinated
OL,4,Cstrikes until summer unless Government
OL,5,Cagrees pay rises
